      "author": "o1xhack",
      "description": "## What's new\n\n- Create daily notes at a configurable local time on desktop, even when Obsidian stays open across multiple days.\n- Schedule one next-run timeout instead of frequent polling, and recalibrate after sleep or window focus.\n- Keep startup creation and optional missed-note backfill while serializing vault checks to prevent duplicate creation.\n- Add automated coverage for local-time validation, once-per-day execution, and next-run scheduling.",
